n: left; vertical-align: top\"><b>Notes:</b>\n</td>\n<td><div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">King Harwyn Hoare is known to have had at least one salt wife.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">King Harren Hoare is known to have had at least four sons.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Qhorwyn_Hoare&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Qhorwyn and his son <a href=\"/index.php/Harwyn_Hoare\" title=\"Harwyn Hoare\">Harwyn</a> may have been inspired by King <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frederick_William_I_of_Prussia\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Frederick William I of Prussia\">Frederick William I of Prussia</a> and his son <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frederick_the_Great\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Frederick the Great\">Frederick II</a>. Frederick William reformed and expanded the Prussian military, and Frederick the Great conquered <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Silesian_Wars\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Silesian Wars\">Silesia</a> soon after coming to the throne.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Qhorwyn_Hoare&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class